reviews.text: We got the combination tempura, dragon roll, lemonade roll and the combination yaki Udon. They were all sooo good and delicious! No left over to take home! We will be coming back to try other menu items!

Pleasant atmosphere and server. Nice presentation of food and tasty! Had the crystal shrimp hand roll. Offered a special buy one get one on the Las Vegas roll, ordered to take home. Will come back again

I had the Japanese katsu curry and it was fantastic! The curry itself was rich and flavorful, with a perfect balance of spices and a hearty mix of potatoes and carrots. The katsu chicken was incredibly tender but still had a very crispy crunch to it. The portion size was generous, and considering the quality, the price was more than fair. Definitely one of the better katsu curries I've had, and I‚Äôll be coming back for more!
Great Food! Was honestly surprised at how good it was. Good prices.the shushi was pretty good not incredible. The donburi and katsu don were amazing.
We came in with a large group and the seating and service were excellent. Sushi was fresh, would definitely go again!

detailedReviews.author: mary castorani
detailedReviews.text: If you are looking for a cozy, inviting Japanese sit down, this is the place. I got their katsu curry lunch and an order of extra rice, completely filled for 14 dollars. The curry was incredibly sweet and to dip with the crunchy katsu was a comfort. The interior is very spacious and easy to get to. I will absolutely be coming back again

detailedReviews.author: Matthew Petersen
detailedReviews.text:
Ate there with some work colleagues and truthfully it was the worst restaurant I have eaten at in three years.

I ate a teriyaki chicken bowl and three sushi rolls.

Teriyaki sizing portions were lousy the chicken was a 6 out of 10. The sushi rolls were each a fail and a 2 out of 10. The fish was old and disgusting and flavourless. Literally every restaurant I have ever been to is better than this one. I have no idea how people are rating this place so high when we are so fortunate to have so many great options for Japanese Teppanyaki and sushi everywhere else in Utah County and Salt Lake County!

detailedReviews.author: ceec k.
detailedReviews.text: the pork katsu curry was fantastic, probably the best japanese curry I've had in the provo area. came with miso soup and a small salad. great food for a great price, and service was wonderful as well!

detailedReviews.author: Haley Hansen
detailedReviews.text: The owners are so nice. They came out to introduce themselves. The food was delicious and authentic.

detailedReviews.author: Ethan Edwards
detailedReviews.text: I LOVE going here! It's very well-priced and one of my favorite places to go for lunch! My favorite dish is the chicken katsu udon soup! So good!!

detailedReviews.author: David Jorgensen
detailedReviews.text:
If you are looking for Japanese donburi or bento, this place won't knock your socks off, but it may scratch the itch.

I ordered salmon donburi. Flavor was pleasant, but rice was low quality and salmon was so undercooked that it was mushy. Tempura vegetables were good though, fresh and crisp. Staff was friendly, food came out quick. Good fish is hard to find in Utah, so my choice was risky in the first place‚Äîmy brother picked a chicken-based dish, and he seemed happy with it. If I go again, I'll try something a little safer, like chicken or pork.

detailedReviews.author: Hannah Mitchell
detailedReviews.text: Such friendly staff!! Truly went above and beyond for me and my sister today!

detailedReviews.author: Rosa Cazorla
detailedReviews.text: This is my favorite Japanese restaurant. Giving 5 stars on everything because it‚Äôs really this good. The service is excellent, the food is super good, and the vibe is very relaxing (especially if you come for lunch) I love their lunch special bento boxes. Good prices and amazing food. I hope they stay around for forever! If you‚Äôve never been, you really need to try it.

detailedReviews.author: Brayden Woodall
detailedReviews.text: The nicest people and the Katsu Donburi is one of the best I have ever eaten.

detailedReviews.author: Megan Askew
detailedReviews.text: My family and I have gone to Demae for nearly 30 years. Food is fresh and delicious; everything from sushi, tempura, udon soups, tonkatsu, and more! We highly recommend Demae!

detailedReviews.author: Elizabeth Nielson
detailedReviews.text:
Went here almost 20 years ago‚Ä¶then back in Provo for a weekend, we decided to give it another go. It was good then and it is good now. We were not disappointed.
The service was good and kind and the food was delicious‚Äîwe are wondering why more people don‚Äôt frequent this place. Yes, the decor is dated, but it was clean.
We each got a Bento Box along with some sushi and tempura. So glad we went to Demae. I‚Äôll be back again soon.

detailedReviews.text: Overall a nice experience.  Food is good quality.  The restaurant is decently clean, but not perfect.  It's very nice and quiet inside.  Decent balance of price and quantity.  Flavors are real and pleasant.  It's been my daughter's favorite on many occasions.
